.Im MicroEmacs command|region
.ds C0 "(\fB\*e\*cc\fR)\ \&
.so me.tni
.TH count-words 2
.XI count-words - "\*(C0Count the number of words in a region"
.SH NAME
count-words \- Count the number of words in a region
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.B count-words
(\fB\*e\*cc\fR)
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B count-words
Counts the  number of  words  between the
.Ht set-mark 2
position and the current cursor position. The command also gives statistics on
the  number of  characters  and the  average  characters  per word. The output
appears on the message line in a format such as:-
.IP
.C "54 Words, 345 Chars, 8 Lines"
.PP
.Ht $result 5
is set to the same output string.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht $result 5 ,
.Ht buffer-info 2 ,
.Ht set-mark 2 .
.ad
.rm C0
.FH
